      itineraire: "Your driver picks you up at your address in Torcy and heads west on the A4 motorway towards Paris. The A4 runs a direct course along the Marne valley, passing the interchanges at Noisy-le-Grand and Joinville-le-Pont before approaching the capital. Depending on your final destination, the driver will exit at Porte de Bercy (for south-east Paris and the Left Bank) or Porte de Vincennes (for eastern and northern Paris). In normal traffic conditions, the journey takes around 25 minutes; during weekday rush hours (7:30-9:30am and 5:30-7:30pm), allow up to 40 minutes. Tolls of approximately 3 euros on the A4 are included in the fixed fare.",
      conseils: "The Vaires-Torcy leisure base, which served as the Paris 2024 Olympic venue for rowing and canoe-kayak, is open to the public for water sports, swimming in summer and cycling on its woodland trails. The Torcy RER A station provides a reliable rail link to Paris in 30 minutes for day-to-day commuting. The Bay 2 shopping centre, located near the station, is one of the largest in the eastern suburbs with a wide range of shops and restaurants. Disneyland Paris is just 15 minutes away by car, making Torcy a practical base for theme park visitors. For the smoothest taxi ride to Paris, consider departing before 7:30am or after 9:30am to avoid the worst of the morning rush.",
